---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Flynt AI — Client Acquisition Intelligence for Recruiters & Sales Teams"
  description="Flynt identifies who needs you before they know they need you. The AI intelligence layer built exclusively for client acquisition."
>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  SECTION 01 — HERO
───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero__content">
      <div class="tag fade-up fade-up-1">Client Acquisition Intelligence</div>
      <h1 class="hero__headline fade-up fade-up-2">
        Flynt identifies who needs you<br />
        <span class="hero__headline-accent">before they know they need you.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero__sub fade-up fade-up-3">
        The AI intelligence layer built exclusively for client acquisition. Flynt continuously surfaces structured, signal-driven client opportunities for recruiters, sales teams, and GTM operators — so your team spends time closing new business, not buried in research.
      </p>
      <div class="hero__ctas fade-up fade-up-4">
        <a href="https://tryflynt.ai/" class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">Start for Free</a>
        <a href="#how-it-works" class="btn btn--outline btn--lg">See How Flynt Works →</a>
      </div>
      <p class="hero__social-proof fade-up fade-up-4">
        Trusted by recruiters, agency operators, and GTM teams.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  SECTION 02 — POSITIONING STRIP
───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="positioning">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="positioning__headline">Built for one purpose: winning new clients.</p>
    <div class="positioning__grid">
      <div class="positioning__card">
        <span class="positioning__not">Not a database.</span>
        <p>Flynt is not a contact database and it is not a candidate sourcing tool. It is a continuously running intelligence system that maps potential client accounts to your exact acquisition criteria.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="positioning__card">
        <span class="positioning__not">Not an outreach tool.</span>
        <p>Flynt does not send messages or run campaigns. It prepares the intelligence that makes every message you send more precise.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="positioning__card">
        <span class="positioning__not">Not another automation.</span>
        <p>Flynt is infrastructure — the intelligence layer that sits beneath your stack and makes everything else sharper, faster, and more consistent.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  SECTION 03 — WHAT FLYNT DOES
───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section what-flynt-does">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="what__layout">
      <div class="what__left">
        <div class="tag">What Flynt Does</div>
        <h2>The intelligence layer between you and your next client.</h2>
        <p class="what__intro">
          Most operators know which types of companies make great clients. The problem is time. Manual research, rebuilt lists, and scattered signals eat the hours that should go toward client conversations.
        </p>
        <p>
          Flynt eliminates that entirely. From the moment it is configured to your target client market, it begins mapping prospect accounts, identifying the right decision-makers to approach, and monitoring signals that indicate a company is ready to become a client — with no manual input required.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
          It does not wait for you to tell it what to research. It runs in the background so that every morning you arrive to a structured, prioritised list of client acquisition opportunities — ready to reach out.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="what__right">
        <ul class="capability-list">
          <li>
            <span class="capability-dot"></span>
            Maps and monitors potential client accounts aligned to your ideal client profile
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="capability-dot"></span>
            Identifies the right decision-makers at each target company for your business development outreach
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="capability-dot"></span>
            Detects hiring signals, growth signals, and company-level triggers that indicate a business is ready for your services
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="capability-dot"></span>
            Structures client prospect data into clean, actionable intelligence — not raw, unsorted lists
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="capability-dot"></span>
            Maintains a continuously updated pipeline of warm client acquisition opportunities over time
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="capability-dot"></span>
            Prepares context so every client outreach conversation can be specific, informed, and timely
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  SECTION 04 — HOW FLYNT WORKS
───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section section--gray how-it-works" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header section-header--center">
      <div class="tag">How It Works</div>
      <h2>Intelligence that runs while you build.</h2>
      <p>Define your ideal client profile once. Flynt handles client acquisition research continuously — delivering structured, signal-rich prospect intelligence so your time stays where it belongs: in conversations that win new business.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step__number">01</div>
        <h3>Define Your Ideal Client Profile</h3>
        <p>Tell Flynt what your ideal client looks like — industries, company types, decision-maker roles, geography, company size. Flynt maps your client acquisition targets, not surface-level keyword lists. One-time setup. Continuously refined as your business grows.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step__connector"></div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step__number">02</div>
        <h3>Client Intelligence Runs Continuously</h3>
        <p>Flynt operates in the background — identifying prospect companies, detecting signals that indicate readiness to buy, and structuring your client pipeline into a clean, prioritised daily flow. No manual list building. No repetitive research sessions. No fragile spreadsheets.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step__connector"></div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step__number">03</div>
        <h3>Reach Out With Precision</h3>
        <p>Flynt prepares structured client intelligence. Your team activates it through the tools you already use — CRM, email platform, sales engagement system. Every outreach starts with context: who to contact, why the timing is right, and what signal triggered the opportunity.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  SECTION 05 — WHO FLYNT IS BUILT FOR
───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section built-for">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header section-header--center">
      <div class="tag">Who It's For</div>
      <h2>Built for operators who win with intelligence.</h2>
      <p>Purpose-built for operators whose revenue depends on winning new business — not a general-purpose prospecting tool.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="audience-grid">
      <div class="audience-card">
        <div class="audience-card__icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Recruiters & Recruitment Agencies</h3>
        <p>Solo recruiters and boutique agencies actively developing new client relationships. Flynt identifies companies that are likely to need your recruiting services — so your business development motion starts with intelligence, not a blank spreadsheet. Flynt finds your clients. You place the candidates.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="audience-card">
        <div class="audience-card__icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Sales & Go-to-Market Teams</h3>
        <p>BDMs, SDR teams, and GTM operators who need account intelligence before every touch. Flynt surfaces the right accounts, at the right moment, with the right context — so outbound is informed before it begins.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="audience-card">
        <div class="audience-card__icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-5 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Agency Owners & Operators</h3>
        <p>Founders and principals running lean teams who cannot afford hours lost to client research. Flynt is the client acquisition intelligence infrastructure that scales without adding headcount — delivering a consistent, structured pipeline of prospective clients regardless of team size.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="audience-card">
        <div class="audience-card__icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Revenue Leaders Building Systems</h3>
        <p>Leaders building repeatable, scalable systems for winning new clients. Flynt provides the intelligence backbone that makes client acquisition systematic, consistent, and compounding — replacing the reactive, random approach that most teams default to.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="audience-qualifier">
      If your growth depends on consistently winning new clients — Flynt is built for you. If you are a recruiter looking to source candidates, Flynt is not the right tool.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  SECTION 06 — WHO FLYNT IS NOT FOR
───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section section--gray not-for">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="not-for__layout">
      <div class="not-for__left">
        <div class="tag">Honest by design</div>
        <h2>Flynt is not for everyone.<br /><span style="color: var(--gray-400)">That's intentional.</span></h2>
        <p>Flynt is built to strengthen disciplined operators — not to replace the judgment, strategy, and execution that revenue work requires.</p>
        <blockquote class="not-for__quote">
          Flynt prepares opportunity. Your team converts it. The best results come from operators who understand the difference — and show up to execute.
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      <div class="not-for__right">
        <p class="not-for__list-label">Flynt is not a fit if you are:</p>
        <ul class="not-for__list">
          <li>A recruiter looking to source candidates or build talent pipelines — Flynt is for client acquisition, not candidate research</li>
          <li>A team expecting guaranteed clients, guaranteed revenue, or instant results</li>
          <li>An operator unwilling to follow up consistently or refine client targeting over time</li>
          <li>Looking for AI to replace the skill of selling, positioning, or relationship-building</li>
          <li>Wanting a fully automated system that removes human judgment from the client acquisition process</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  SECTION 10 — FINAL CTA
───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="final-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="final-cta__inner">
      <h2>Stop researching.<br />Start closing.</h2>
      <p>Your next client is already in the market. Flynt finds the signal before they find someone else.</p>
      <a href="https://tryflynt.ai/" class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">Start for Free →</a>
      <span class="final-cta__disclaimer">No credit card required. Cancel anytime.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
/* ── Hero ── */
.hero {
  padding: 80px 24px 96px;
  background: var(--white);
}

.hero__content {
  max-width: 760px;
}

.hero__headline {
  margin: 8px 0 24px;
}

.hero__headline-accent {
  color: var(--purple);
}

.hero__sub {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  max-width: 620px;
  margin-bottom: 36px;
  color: var(--gray-600);
}

.hero__ctas {
  display: flex;
  gap: 12px;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}

.hero__social-proof {
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: var(--gray-400);
}

/* ── Positioning Strip ── */
.positioning {
  background: var(--purple-bg);
  padding: 56px 24px;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--purple-bg-2);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--purple-bg-2);
}

.positioning .container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 36px;
}

.positioning__headline {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--purple);
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}

.positioning__grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 32px;
}

.positioning__card {}

.positioning__not {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--black);
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.positioning__card p {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--gray-600);
}

/* ── What Flynt Does ── */
.what__layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 72px;
  align-items: start;
}

.what__left h2 {
  margin: 12px 0 20px;
}

.what__intro {
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.capability-list {
  list-style: none;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 20px;
  padding: 32px;
  background: var(--gray-50);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
}

.capability-list li {
  display: flex;
  gap: 14px;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--gray-700, #374151);
  align-items: flex-start;
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.capability-dot {
  width: 8px;
  height: 8px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--purple);
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 6px;
}

/* ── How It Works ── */
.steps {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr;
  gap: 0;
  align-items: start;
}

.step {
  background: var(--white);
  border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  padding: 32px;
}

.step__number {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  color: var(--purple);
  opacity: 0.25;
  line-height: 1;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.step h3 {
  margin-bottom: 12px;
  font-size: 1.1rem;
}

.step p {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
}

.step__connector {
  width: 40px;
  height: 1px;
  background: var(--gray-200);
  margin-top: 56px;
}

/* ── Audience ── */
.audience-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 20px;
  margin-bottom: 32px;
}

.audience-card {
  background: var(--white);
  border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  padding: 28px;
  transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
}

.audience-card:hover {
  border-color: var(--purple-light);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-purple);
}

.audience-card__icon {
  width: 44px;
  height: 44px;
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  background: var(--purple-bg);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  color: var(--purple);
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.audience-card h3 {
  font-size: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.audience-card p {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
}

.audience-qualifier {
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--gray-600);
  padding: 20px 32px;
  background: var(--purple-bg);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  border: 1px solid var(--purple-bg-2);
}

/* ── Not For ── */
.not-for__layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 72px;
  align-items: start;
}

.not-for__left h2 {
  margin: 12px 0 16px;
}

.not-for__quote {
  margin-top: 24px;
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--gray-600);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--purple);
  padding-left: 20px;
  line-height: 1.6;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
}

.not-for__list-label {
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--gray-800);
  margin-bottom: 16px;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
}

.not-for__list {
  list-style: none;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 14px;
}

.not-for__list li {
  display: flex;
  gap: 12px;
  font-size: 0.92rem;
  color: var(--gray-600);
  align-items: flex-start;
  padding-left: 0;
}

.not-for__list li::before {
  content: '✕';
  color: var(--gray-400);
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 2px;
}

/* ── Final CTA ── */
.final-cta {
  background: var(--black);
  padding: 96px 24px;
}

.final-cta__inner {
  max-width: var(--max-width);
  margin: 0 auto;
  text-align: center;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 20px;
}

.final-cta__inner h2 {
  color: white;
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.2rem);
}

.final-cta__inner p {
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  max-width: 480px;
}

.final-cta__disclaimer {
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
}

/* ── Responsive ── */
@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .positioning__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .what__layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 40px; }
  .steps {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .step__connector { display: none; }
  .audience-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .not-for__layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 40px; }
}
</style>
